caroCN 
The act of creating; 
inf. n. of caraOa. (Ṣ, M, Mṣb.)

entry.sense:
And it is used also to signify Women; 
[because they are the sources of offspring;] (T, Mgh, TA;) like as samaMCN is used to signify “rain:” (TA:) as in the saying of ʼOmar, Huj-uwA biAlc-ur-iy-api [Perform ye the pilgrimage with the women]. 
(T, Mgh, TA. [See his saying in full, voce riboqN.])

